Police were responded about 6:30 p.m. to the report of an attack near the intersection of Main Street and Venice Way. A 19-year-old man was approached by the robber who used bodily force to steal his money. The victim was taken to a local hospital in unknown condition. The attacker, who has not been caught, was described as a black man about 25 years old with black hair and brown eyes. He stood 6 feet tall and weighed about 170 pounds -LAPD 